<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,934,1067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="535">
The genus was up to now known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[646,752,934,959]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="535">Australia</collectingCountry>
, where 
<number box="[838,866,935,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="535" value="10.0">10</number>
species were recorded (
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer" box="[1136,1300,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="535" refString="Spencer, K. (1986) The Australian Chloropinae (Diptera, Chloropidae). Journal of Natural History, 20 (3), 503 - 615. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938600770401" type="journal article" year="1986">
Spencer, 
<number box="[1240,1300,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="535" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus was considered restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[471,574,970,995]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="535">Australia</collectingCountry>
with records throughout the country from Tasmania to Queensland and west to Western 
<collectingCountry box="[279,385,1006,1031]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="535">Australia</collectingCountry>
, but has not been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[693,914,1006,1031]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="1" pageNumber="535">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer" box="[926,1099,1006,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="535" refString="Spencer, K. (1986) The Australian Chloropinae (Diptera, Chloropidae). Journal of Natural History, 20 (3), 503 - 615. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938600770401" type="journal article" year="1986">
Spencer (
<number box="[1032,1091,1006,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="535" value="1986.0">1986</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
keyed the Australian species. This is the first record of the genus in the Oriental Region.
</paragraph>
